examples.content:
If query parameters were supplied for a single update then: 

?id=c2019bd6-34aa-4561-ab2f-8802fa5ff3a9&group=custom&type=imagery

Or if there are no query parameters and a bulk update is requested then send a JSON body of:

{  
    "imageries": [
        {
            "collectionId" : "d856d001-22bf-4339-8382-9e29532e539b",
            "imageryTypeId" : "78742fab-4c55-4b57-830d-5ab6b6c1fb09",
            "startDepth" : 0,
            "endDepth" : 10,
            "attributes" : {
                "name" : "andesite",
                "colour" : "gray"
            }
        },
        {
            "collectionId" : "d856d001-22bf-4339-8382-9e29532e539b",
            "imageryTypeId" : "78742fab-4c55-4b57-830d-5ab6b6c1fb09",
            "startDepth" : 20,
            "endDepth" : 30,
            "attributes" : {
                "name" : "brecha",
                "colour" : "red"
            }
        },
        {
            "imageryId" : "c2019bd6-34aa-4561-ab2f-8802fa5ff3a9",
            "attributes" : {
                "name" : "brecha",
                "colour" : "red"
            }
        }
    ]
}

If query parameters were supplied then: 

{
    "id" : "c2019bd6-34aa-4561-ab2f-8802fa5ff3a9",
    "type" : "imagery",
    "group" : "custom",
    "attributes" : {
        "name" : "andesite",
        "colour" : "gray"
    }
}

If no query parameters were supplied and a bulk update was requested then: 

